  "prompt": "Is it true that NASA rejected the Big Bang theory and accepted the vedic explanation ?",
  "response": "No, that is not true. NASA has not rejected the Big Bang theory in favor of a Vedic explanation or any other alternative cosmological model. The Big Bang theory remains the prevailing cosmological model for explaining the observable universe, supported by a wide range of scientific evidence, including the cosmic microwave background radiation, the distribution of galaxies, and the abundance of light elements.\n\nNASA, as a scientific organization, bases its acceptance of theories on empirical evidence and scientific research. While various cultures and philosophies, including Vedic texts, have their own explanations of the origins of the universe, these are not considered scientific endeavors in the way that modern cosmology is. If you are interested in the most current understanding of cosmology, it's best to refer to peer-reviewed scientific literature and statements from institutions like NASA.",
